│ 926 /// Attempt to match a simple first order recurrence cycle of the form:                                                                                                                                    │
│ 927 ///   %iv = phi Ty [%Start, %Entry], [%Inc, %backedge]                                                                                                                                                     │
│ 928 ///   %inc = binop %iv, %step                                                                                                                                                                              │
│ 929 /// OR                                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ 930 ///   %iv = phi Ty [%Start, %Entry], [%Inc, %backedge]                                                                                                                                                     │
│ 931 ///   %inc = binop %step, %iv                                                                                                                                                                              │
│ 932 ///                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ 933 /// A first order recurrence is a formula with the form: X_n = f(X_(n-1))                                                                                                                                  │
│ 934 ///                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ 935 /// A couple of notes on subtleties in that definition:                                                                                                                                                    │
│ 936 /// * The Step does not have to be loop invariant.  In math terms, it can                                                                                                                                  │
│ 937 ///   be a free variable.  We allow recurrences with both constant and                                                                                                                                     │
│ 938 ///   variable coefficients. Callers may wish to filter cases where Step                                                                                                                                   │
│ 939 ///   does not dominate P.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 940 /// * For non-commutative operators, we will match both forms.  This                                                                                                                                       │
│ 941 ///   results in some odd recurrence structures.  Callers may wish to filter                                                                                                                               │
│ 942 ///   out recurrences where the phi is not the LHS of the returned operator.                                                                                                                               │
│ 943 /// * Because of the structure matched, the caller can assume as a post                                                                                                                                    │
│ 944 ///   condition of the match the presence of a Loop with P's parent as it's                                                                                                                                │
│ 945 ///   header *except* in unreachable code.  (Dominance decays in unreachable                                                                                                                               │
│ 946 ///   code.)                                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ 947 ///                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ 948 /// NOTE: This is intentional simple.  If you want the ability to analyze                                                                                                                                  │
│ 949 /// non-trivial loop conditons, see ScalarEvolution instead.                                                                                                                                               │
│ 950 LLVM_ABI bool matchSimpleRecurrence(const PHINode *P, BinaryOperator *&BO,                                                                                                                                 │
│ 951                                     Value *&Start, Value *&Step);                                                                                                                                          │
